sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM covid_metrics 
WHERE reproduction_rate > 1.2;

SELECT stringency_index, date
FROM stringency_measures
WHERE country_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
Countries have unique ISO 3166-1 alpha-3 codes; 
COVID-19 metrics are often analyzed by country to understand the spread and impact of the pandemic; 
The rate of new tests per thousand residents is a key metric in assessing the extent of testing within a population.
